wiki.content: “feel something” talks about fear and anxiety in a person, where that person has reached a limit in life where people, even close people, cannot be trusted. Bea tells us about when you have reached a point of your life where you can not feel any emotion or even pain or happiness, you feel empty inside, you just want to feel something, be it joy or sadness. Bea talks about the song via Twitter: "i’ve been trying to cope with the mediocrity of life because recently it hasn’t been a sad experience but it hasn’t been a happy one either. i tried my best to put that into words almost selfishly because i wanted to know if i’m the problem or if we all go through it." Can you describe your experience releasing the song “feel something” last summer, and watching it gradually find a larger audience this year? "I never expected any song I create to reach so many people, especially when a song is a year old. I’m still surprised and grateful every day." –via Billboard (2020) Read more on Last.fm.
